Subject: [PATCH 2/2] fix(phase-1): remove @prisma/client imports and fix
 Header crash
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Backend — 4 files:
- common/decorators/roles.decorator.ts
    BEFORE: import { UserRole } from '@prisma/client'
    AFTER:  export type UserRole = 'ADMIN'|'CASHIER'|'WAREHOUSE'|'BRANCH_MANAGER'
    EFFECT: was causing build error TS2305 on every npm run build

- modules/sales/dto/create-sale.dto.ts
    BEFORE: import { PaymentMethod } from '@prisma/client'
    AFTER:  local enum PaymentMethod { CASH, CARD, BANK_TRANSFER, CREDIT, MIXED }
    EFFECT: was causing build error TS2305; enum values match PostgreSQL payment_method type

- modules/sales/dto/refund-sale.dto.ts
    BEFORE: import { PaymentMethod } from '@prisma/client'
    AFTER:  import { PaymentMethod } from './create-sale.dto'
    EFFECT: re-uses the locally defined enum; no duplication

- modules/sales/dto/sale-query.dto.ts
    BEFORE: import { SaleStatus } from '@prisma/client'
    AFTER:  local enum SaleStatus { DRAFT, COMPLETED, REFUNDED, PARTIALLY_REFUNDED, CANCELLED }
    EFFECT: was causing build error TS2305; values match PostgreSQL sale_status type

Frontend — 1 file:
- components/layout/Header.tsx line 70
    BEFORE: {user.fullName[0]}
    AFTER:  {(user.fullName || user.username || 'U')[0].toUpperCase()}
    EFFECT: was throwing TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading '0')
            because backend returns full_name (snake_case) but User type expects
            fullName (camelCase) — guard prevents crash on any field mapping issue

Build results:
- backend:  npm run build → EXIT 0, 0 errors
- frontend: npm run build → EXIT 0, 13 pages compiled
